ANSWER\
Java Program to check whether a number is even and also a multiple of 11 using nested-if:\
\
Code:\
\
public class EvenAndMultipleOf11 \{\
    public static void main(String[] args) \{\
        int number = 66; // You can change the number for testing\
\
        if (number % 2 == 0) \{\
            if (number % 11 == 0) \{\
                System.out.println(number + " is even and also a multiple of 11.");\
            \} else \{\
                System.out.println(number + " is even but not a multiple of 11.");\
            \}\
        \} else \{\
            System.out.println(number + " is not even.");\
        \}\
    \}\
\}\
\
Explanation:\
\
The outer if checks if the number is even using number % 2 == 0.\
\
The inner if checks if it's also a multiple of 11 using number % 11 == 0.\
\
This is a classic use case of nested-if statements.\
\
\
Sample Output:\
\
66 is even and also a multiple of 11.\
\
