java Program to identify the largest number using Ternary Operator:\
\
Code:\
\
public class LargestUsingTernary \{\
    public static void main(String[] args) \{\
        int num1 = 25;\
        int num2 = 45;\
\
        int largest = (num1 > num2) ? num1 : num2;\
\
        System.out.println("The largest number is: " + largest);\
    \}\
\}\
\
Explanation:\
\
The ternary operator syntax: (condition) ? value_if_true : value_if_false.\
\
Here, it checks if num1 > num2 and returns the larger one.\
\
It's a compact alternative to using if-else statements.\
\
\
Sample Output:\
\
The largest number is: 45\
